<TITLE> Another new party emerges, third since Jan 11 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com) Another new political party has emerged, naming itself the Bangladesh Guardian Party (BGP), through the ongoing ban on indoor politics. Convenor A T M Shafiuddin, not a known political figure within the country's political arena, announced the creation of the party at a press conference at the Jatiya Press Club Friday. "Patriotism and honesty will be the party's ideals while the goal of the party is ensuring people's welfare through practice of proper democracy," said the new party's press release. In a written statement, Shafiuddin said: "We have decided to get involved in politics considering the country's negative political culture. We will devote ourselves to guaranteeing the welfare of the people." With the emergence of the BGP, the number of new parties formed amid the state of emergency since Jan 11, reaches three. On July 19, a former Jatiya Party leader Shawkat Hossain Nilu declared the founding of the National Peoples Party. Two days later, a former BNP leader Ferdous Ahmed Quraishi floated a new party named the Progressive Democratic Party. b
